---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Abhishek Mohanty — Oracle HCM Cloud Technical Lead, Oracle ACE Apprentice, AIOUG member.">
  <article class="about container">
    <div class="avatar" aria-hidden="true">AM</div>
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p class="role">Oracle HCM Cloud Consultant &amp; Technical Architect</p>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Deep expertise in Oracle HCM Cloud — Fast Formulas, HDL Transformations, Benefits, Payroll,
        and Recruiting configurations. I share practical, real-world solutions for HCM Cloud
        consultants navigating complex implementations across the APAC region.
      </p>

      <p>
        I'm an <strong>Oracle ACE Apprentice</strong> and a member of the
        <strong>All India Oracle Users Group (AIOUG)</strong>. Over the last decade I've worked
        across most of the modules in Oracle HCM Cloud — Core HR, Absence Management, Time and
        Labor, Compensation, Benefits, Payroll, Recruiting, Redwood, HDL, and OTBI — with a
        heavy lean toward the techno-functional side. Most of my recent delivery has been
        multi-country APAC implementations: Taiwan, Singapore, Malaysia, Philippines, Hong Kong,
        Thailand.
      </p>

      <h2>Why this site exists</h2>
      <p>
        Oracle's documentation is excellent at telling you <em>what</em> a feature does, and
        mostly silent on the <em>edges</em> — the way <code>IV_ACCRUAL</code> actually behaves
        inside a matrix accrual, why <code>ESS_LOG_WRITE</code> blows up in 26A when used inside
        a Global Absence Carryover formula, what happens to
        <code>PER_ASG_REL_ORIGINAL_DATE_OF_HIRE</code> after a Global Transfer. These are the
        things I write down here.
      </p>

      <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Production-ready Fast Formulas with named-employee worked examples</li>
        <li>Debug logging idioms for every formula type that has them</li>
        <li>Multi-country APAC patterns — leave policies, accrual matrices, TER/TCR</li>
        <li>Redwood and HDL Transformation Formula notes</li>
      </ul>

      <hr />
      <p class="disclaimer">
        Notes on this site are personal and reflect the author's views, not those of any
        employer or client. Oracle and the Oracle product names referenced are trademarks of
        Oracle Corporation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 720px;
    padding-block: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);
  }
  .avatar {
    width: 110px;
    height: 110px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--bg-dark);
    color: white;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 2.4rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(26,26,26,0.15);
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.4rem);
    margin: 0 0 0.4em;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }
  .role {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--orange);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }
  .prose {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2.2em;
    border: none;
  }
  .disclaimer {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
